President Joe Biden delivered a speech at the National Education Association (NEA) headquarters in Washington, D.C. In his speech, he touched on various topics such as the upcoming midterm elections, gun safety, climate change, democracy, and the economy. He criticized MAGA Republicans for their stance on abortion, gun control, and defunding the FBI. Biden also highlighted the achievements of his administration, including the American Rescue Plan, infrastructure investments, and efforts to lower prescription drug costs. He emphasized the need to protect democracy and restore faith in elections. The President ended his speech with a message of hope and unity, expressing his optimism for the future of the United States.